## Write a program to convert string to pathcase

Pathcase is a style of writing in which all letters are lowercase and spaces are replaced with forward slashes.

```
Input  : "hello world"
Output : "hello/world"
```

---

<CodeBlock slug="convert-string-to-pathcase" >

```cpp
#include <cstring>
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
 
int main()
{
    string str;
    getline(cin, str);
    for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); ++i) {
        if (str[i] == ' ') {
            str[i] = '/';
        }
    }
    cout << str << endl;
    return 0;
}
```

